<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1782" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1782">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/168.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">President of Salvador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For Mrs. Knox and myself I thank you for your courteous telegram of
                            congratulation and assure you that I shall always remember kindness of
                            yourself and the people of Salvador during my visit.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>